{"tid":2431533,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"美國都頂唔順，各州都鬥快解封，話之你個提意","createTime":"2021-03-03T17:17:03.000Z","updateTime":"2021-03-04T00:51:45.000Z","uid":130105,"like":6,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":11,"replies":[{"pid":"b7b683bf1b5105caac215d8313d95e5a02a2657b","tid":2431533,"uid":130105,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-03-03T17:17:03.000Z","msg":"冇乜人理登登個提意<br />\n======================================<br />\n&bull;Biden urged Americans not to let their guard down as COVID-19 infections fall and vaccinations ramp up<br />\n&bull;Came as Texas and Mississippi governors announced they were lifting all restrictions and mask mandates  <br />\n&bull;Meanwhile, Michigan and Louisiana have relaxed rules on bars, restaurants and other businesses<br />\n&bull;Massachusetts has lifted restaurant capacity limits and South Carolina erased limits on gatherings  <br />\n&bull;The loosening of COVID restrictions across the country comes despite pleas from health officials<br />\n&bull;CDC Director Dr Rochelle Walensky warned cases could spike again if restrictions are eased too quickly <br />\n&bull;US cases have plunged more than 70% in two months from an average of nearly 250,000 new infections a day<br />\n&bull;The average deaths per day have plummeted about 40% since mid-January<br />\n&bull;The current nationwide average COVID numbers are at 2,000 deaths per day and 68,000 cases per day<br />\n&bull;While cases are plunging nationally, Texas and Mississippi are among a handful of states that have seen a slight uptick in new infections and deaths in recent days <br />\n&bull;Biden said the US is now on track to vaccinate all adults by the end of May after he invoked the Defense Production Act to speed up the manufacturing of Johnson &amp; Johnson's newly-approved one-dose shot <br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/03/13/39992346-9320949-image-m-15_1614777822486.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2021%2F03%2F03%2F13%2F39992346-9320949-image-m-15_1614777822486.jpg&h=8cda818f&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n President Joe Biden has urged Americans not to let their guard down even as COVID-19 infections plummet and vaccinations ramp up<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/03/13/39962766-9320949-Texas_is_lifting_its_mask_mandate_Gov_Greg_Abbott_left_with_Pres-m-20_1614777877292.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2021%2F03%2F03%2F13%2F39962766-9320949-Texas_is_lifting_its_mask_mandate_Gov_Greg_Abbott_left_with_Pres-m-20_1614777877292.jpg&h=9c585111&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Texas is the largest state to do away with mask mandates and restrictions as Gov Greg Abbott declared it was time to 'open Texas 100 percent'. All restrictions in the Lone Star state will end March 10<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/03/13/39963452-9320949-Mississippi_immediately_followed_Texas_decision_Mississippi_Gov_-a-21_1614777880308.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2021%2F03%2F03%2F13%2F39963452-9320949-Mississippi_immediately_followed_Texas_decision_Mississippi_Gov_-a-21_1614777880308.jpg&h=175d437a&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Mississippi Governor Tate Reeves almost immediately followed suit announcing he is rolling back all county mask mandates and removing statewide restrictions on all businesses from today<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/20/39962768-9318245-image-a-49_1614717378735.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2021%2F03%2F02%2F20%2F39962768-9318245-image-a-49_1614717378735.jpg&h=a3833e24&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/20/39963310-9318245-image-a-68_1614718582222.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2021%2F03%2F02%2F20%2F39963310-9318245-image-a-68_1614718582222.jpg&h=d5c01806&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/21/39964264-9318245-image-a-74_1614720324195.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2021%2F03%2F02%2F21%2F39964264-9318245-image-a-74_1614720324195.jpg&h=9abd788f&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Texas will also do away with limits on the number of diners that businesses can serve indoors, said Abbott, who made the announcement at a restaurant in Lubbock. People sit at a bar and restaurant in Austin, Texas, in June 2020<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/21/39964262-9318245-image-a-77_1614720407200.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2021%2F03%2F02%2F21%2F39964262-9318245-image-a-77_1614720407200.jpg&h=b9f94130&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Mississippi reported 301 new infections and 44 deaths on Tuesday. The state has recorded a total of 295,295, infections and 6,724 deaths. Attendees walk through the Mississippi State Fair in Jackson, Mississippi in October 2020<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/03/15/39999694-9320949-image-a-27_1614786099838.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2021%2F03%2F03%2F15%2F39999694-9320949-image-a-27_1614786099838.jpg&h=dfa566f7&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n In Massachusetts, Governor Charlie Baker lifted restaurant capacity limits entirely from Monday (pictured is a Boston restuarnt). Theaters can now open at 50 per cent capacity, with a maximum of 500 people, and capacity limits across all businesses have been raised to 50 per cent<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://videos.dailymail.co.uk/video/mol/2021/03/02/3753511669035910453/1024x576_MP4_3753511669035910453.mp4\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fvideos.dailymail.co.uk%2Fvideo%2Fmol%2F2021%2F03%2F02%2F3753511669035910453%2F1024x576_MP4_3753511669035910453.mp4&d=UjOWczzRfTNgHoC3e3JiXxyAur%2Bbp9MVyOkMM5%2FMxDY%3D&h=a8896bf5\" target=\"_blank\">https://videos.dailymail.co.uk/video/mol/2021/03/02/3753511669035910453/1024x576_MP4_3753511669035910453.mp4</a><br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://videos.dailymail.co.uk/video/mol/2021/03/02/6656641565491508300/1024x576_MP4_6656641565491508300.mp4\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fvideos.dailymail.co.uk%2Fvideo%2Fmol%2F2021%2F03%2F02%2F6656641565491508300%2F1024x576_MP4_6656641565491508300.mp4&d=UjOWczzRfTNgHoC3e3JiXxyAur%2Bbp9MVyOkMM5%2FMxDY%3D&h=3c316e5e\" target=\"_blank\">https://videos.dailymail.co.uk/video/mol/2021/03/02/6656641565491508300/1024x576_MP4_6656641565491508300.mp4</a><br />\n<br />\nsource:<a href=\"https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-9320949/Biden-urges-calm-Texas-Mississippi-lift-COVID-restrictions.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailymail.co.uk%2Fnews%2Farticle-9320949%2FBiden-urges-calm-Texas-Mississippi-lift-COVID-restrictions.html&d=UjOWczzRfTNgHoC3e3JiXxyAur%2Bbp9MVyOkMM5%2FMxDY%3D&h=df181293\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-9320949/Biden-urges-calm-Texas-Mississippi-lift-COVID-restrictions.html</a>"},{"pid":"9e779a4324503e3433c8c8ebb19246f787fb0a99","tid":2431533,"uid":5787,"like":13,"dislike":0,"score":13,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-03-03T22:32:50.000Z","msg":"話時話<br />\n拜登係咪死咗都無人知<br />\n無聲無氣<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f620ed4c048d1fedf5386afc854a5680fdf8bb08","tid":2431533,"uid":126889,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-03-03T22:37:22.000Z","msg":"暗渡陳倉<br />\n一開返世界就唔同樣<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n美國會同中國斷哂關係"},{"pid":"d35bb25cfcbaa62bd97e90a8a3c31cbc0300d62d","tid":2431533,"uid":130105,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"quote":{"pid":"